<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:59PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Carroll, eastern Heard, north central Troup and southwestern Coweta
Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 259 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Handy, or 8 miles
northeast of Franklin, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Newnan, Franklin, Grantville, Centralhatchee, Corinth, East Newnan,
Plant Wansley, Harrisonville, Powers Crossroads and Handy.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
